    <node id="Based on the meeting transcript, Meilyr Rowlands from Estyn has acknowledged that there is a concern about white working-class boys not attaining as they should through the education system. However, Estyn has not specifically looked at white working-class boys in their research or studies. Instead, they have focused on deprived children identified by eligibility for free school meals and have identified good practices that could also benefit this particular cohort. Therefore, while Estyn recognizes the concern about underachievement of white working-class boys, they have not conducted any specific research or identified good practices exclusively for this group." />
