    <node id="1. The current tracking system for previously looked-after children who have since been adopted is not very targeted, as the pupil-level annual school census (PLASC) data does not differentiate whether children are adopted or not. This makes it difficult to track adopted children effectively. However, looked-after children are being tracked by regional consortia.&#10;2. The discussion reveals that there might be a lack of clarity regarding the use of a specific grant for looked-after children who have since been adopted, as opposed to all adopted children. This confusion needs to be addressed directly with the Welsh Government for clarification.&#10;3. While there is room for improvement in tracking previously looked-after children who have been adopted, it is crucial to ensure that any grant specifically targeting looked-after children is used appropriately and effectively to address their unique educational needs." />
