    <edge source="1. The committee will be discussing Estyn's (the education and training inspectorate for Wales) annual report for 2016-17 during this session. They will cover various areas identified in the agenda, raising issues they think appropriate.&#10;2. The witnesses present for this session are Meilyr Rowlands (Chief Inspector), Claire Morgan (Strategic Director), and Simon Brown (Strategic Director) from Estyn." target="Estyn has observed that schools have improved in targeted usage of the pupil development grant funding towards children eligible for free school meals compared to its initial implementation. However, there is still room for better targeting, as some schools interpret poverty more broadly and may not strictly adhere to the definition of free school meals when allocating resources. It is essential to refine the implementation of this approach while maintaining focus on the original target group, including potential adjustments for children who no longer receive free school meals but still require support.">
