    <edge source="1. The committee will be discussing Estyn's (the education and training inspectorate for Wales) annual report for 2016-17 during this session. They will cover various areas identified in the agenda, raising issues they think appropriate.&#10;2. The witnesses present for this session are Meilyr Rowlands (Chief Inspector), Claire Morgan (Strategic Director), and Simon Brown (Strategic Director) from Estyn." target="Professor Donaldson was asked to undertake a review of Estyn's role due to the extensive education reforms and the need for external scrutiny in the current context of rapid educational changes. This was considered important because various aspects of work in the education system, including schools, colleges, and the system as a whole, have changed. The new education reforms require a careful balance between implementing changes and not overburdening teachers and headteachers with excessive workload pressure. Estyn's role in self-improvement adds to this responsibility, making external scrutiny particularly valuable for maintaining focus on continuous evolution and improvement.">
