    <edge source="1. The committee will be discussing Estyn's (the education and training inspectorate for Wales) annual report for 2016-17 during this session. They will cover various areas identified in the agenda, raising issues they think appropriate.&#10;2. The witnesses present for this session are Meilyr Rowlands (Chief Inspector), Claire Morgan (Strategic Director), and Simon Brown (Strategic Director) from Estyn." target="1. Estyn benefits from close working relationships with other education inspectorates such as Ofsted (England), Education Scotland, and the Education Training Inspectorate in Northern Ireland. They learn from each other and have inspectors shadowing and being shadowed during inspections.&#10;2. One unique aspect of Estyn's approach to inspection is their use of nominee and peer inspectors. This involves having a member from the body being inspected as part of the inspection team, allowing them to understand the process and help their organization move forward after the inspection.&#10;3. This approach differs from Ofsted's methods since it incorporates those directly involved in the institution into the evaluation process, fostering better understanding and collaboration during the improvement process.">
