 for primary schools by making key stage 2 results more transparent. However, the specific impact on key stage 2 results is not directly addressed in the transcript.&#10;5. The change was likely made with the intention of encouraging schools to share best practices and learn from higher-performing institutions, fostering a culture of continuous improvement within the education system.">
