    <edge source="Estyn has observed that schools have improved in targeted usage of the pupil development grant funding towards children eligible for free school meals compared to its initial implementation. However, there is still room for better targeting, as some schools interpret poverty more broadly and may not strictly adhere to the definition of free school meals when allocating resources. It is essential to refine the implementation of this approach while maintaining focus on the original target group, including potential adjustments for children who no longer receive free school meals but still require support." target="Professor Donaldson was asked to undertake a review of Estyn's role due to the extensive education reforms and the need for external scrutiny in the current context of rapid educational changes. This was considered important because various aspects of work in the education system, including schools, colleges, and the system as a whole, have changed. The new education reforms require a careful balance between implementing changes and not overburdening teachers and headteachers with excessive workload pressure. Estyn's role in self-improvement adds to this responsibility, making external scrutiny particularly valuable for maintaining focus on continuous evolution and improvement.">
